üèãÔ∏è Solo Practice Drills for Serve & Volley Players
1. Wall Rally Control Drill (15 min)

Hit soft, controlled shots against a wall using a continental grip.
Focus: Keep the ball low and practice blocking rather than swinging.
Challenge: Can you do 10 consecutive controlled "punch" volleys without overhitting?
2. Target Toss & Volley (10 min)

Toss the ball underhand to yourself and practice catching it with the racket face (like a pancake).
Then start adding a light punch to direct it at a target (chalk mark or small object on the ground).
3. Serve Form Isolation (15 min)

Practice the toss without hitting the ball‚Äîyou‚Äôre training for consistent height and placement.
Toss and catch it at eye-level directly above your leading foot.
Then try half-serves (just bringing the racket up and lightly tapping the ball over the net).
4. Shadow Movement & Split Step Drill (5 min)

Without a ball, practice moving from the baseline to the net using a split step before each imagined volley.
Visualize closing the net fast and balanced.
This will make your footwork instinctual during real play.
Would you like me to turn these drills into a printable PDF you can take to the court? Also, do you know your grip size yet or would you like me to show you how to measure it before you pick a racket?

