üéæ Mansour Bahrami: The Court Jester of Tennis
Born on April 26, 1956, in Arak, Iran, Mansour Bahrami's journey to tennis stardom is as unconventional as his playing style. Growing up in a country where tennis was considered an elitist sport, Bahrami taught himself to play using kitchen utensils, as he couldn't afford a racket. His passion and talent eventually led him to represent Iran in the Davis Cup at just 16 years old.
