exouubqaw.blob.core.windows.net
+23
tennissg.com
+23

üîÑ Practicing Grip Transitions
To develop smooth transitions between grips:

Shadow Swings:
Practice switching grips without hitting a ball. Start in your forehand grip and transition to the continental grip as if approaching the net.
Wall Drills:
Stand close to a wall and practice volleys using the continental grip. This reinforces muscle memory for net play.
Grip Awareness:
Regularly check your grip during practice sessions to ensure correct hand placement.
For a comprehensive visual guide, you might find this video helpful:

Feel free to reach out if you have more questions or need further assistance!


